content:
Report on Messaging Activity in Service Cloud

To track your service team's messaging activity, create custom report types on Messaging objects. This applies to various messaging channels including In-App, Web, WhatsApp, Facebook Messenger, SMS, and Bring Your Own Channel.

Consider creating reports based on the following objects:

* MessagingChannel: Represents a communication channel
* ConversationEntry: Represents a message or event in chat history (standard messaging channels only)
* MessagingSession: Represents a session with a messaging user
* MessagingEndUser: Represents a single address communicating with a Messaging channel

Review these sample report configurations for ideas:

* Track average length of closed sessions by channel type
* Track accounts with the most active messaging users
* Track inbound and outbound messages not delivered in standard channels
* Track conversations by channel or channel type
* Track conversations by day or day and by channel

Use Data Cloud to report on enhanced Messaging channel transcripts.
title: Tracking Messaging Activity in Service Cloud
